item.title: BTTF Flux Capacitor Complete Case and parts board
item.description:
Need to make your Flux Capacitor authentic?

This is an almost exact design of the original Flux Capacitor case from the BTTF movies. J1210JPL Stahlin case, with front cover cutout. Also the backer board for mounting the component parts is included.

Inspiration from these websites:
https://www.therpf.com/forums/threads/bttf-flux-capacitor-replica.330326/
https://markus-wobisch.blogspot.com/2018/12/building-bttf-flux-capacitor.html

The whole assembly is included. I will upload a cut up version of all parts so smaller printers can make this case....

Size: 291mm x 345mm x 177mm

When the hinge is printed use a 5/64 inch drill bit (6 inch long) to clear out the hinge pin holes then use 1.75mm filament as the hinge pin...

I am also in the process of designing the interior parts from original drawings and specs.

item.title: Klir Di-4 Adapter Plate Red Sea Reefer 250 V3 Sump
item.description:
I spent many hours mocking this up many different ways in Tinkercad. I spent over 100 hours printing many test versions. I sold one on Ebay that really impressed the buyer who has used it for 6 months now but not much interest there so here it is for free. It is a very tight drop in fit. I use aquarium sealant to close gaps basically anywhere water touches. I ran my last model for 9 months and 3 rolls of fleece. This is my latest design.

Water does leak under the front edge of the tray into where the socks would be and makes some noise. This is why I siliconed the previous version around all edges after pushing it in place. If you can put an even bead of silicone on that edge and let it cure before installing I think it would seal pretty good.

Print time with Prusa slicer.... 20 hours. Sure it could be made thinner etc. but I wanted a solid piece of kit!

item.title: Lifecam VX-3000 Support for Ender 3
item.description:
This is a mount for the Microsoft LifeCam VX-3000 to attach to Ender-3.

Remix of the C270 Webcam support for Ender 3- remodel of the mount only. All other pieces created by OP Waverunner62. Cheers from Canada friend, my name is also Eric!

Used the old mount as a base to expand model to support the shape and size of the webcam I already owned, the Microsoft LifeCam VX-3000.

Printed on Ender-3 Max in about 12 hours in total. There is a clip base and a screw base to screw onto existing printer hardware. I recommend using the 45° angle screw base for stability. Print at least 3 arms for full length and maneuverability. Use supports for the camera mount piece and print vertically aligned for best results. The rest of the pieces are best printed horizontally. Zip-ties for webcam cord is not necessary but can be used if you prefer.

Hardware:
4x M4 30mm bolts
4x M4 Nuts
item.author: lunarLarceny

item.title: lightbearer laser engraver
item.description:
this is a custom core-xy frame for laser engraving. This is, in my honest opinion, the most user friendly frame. Super easy to assemble and minimum adjustment requires on belt tension to get it to work perfectly square. using mgn12 linear rails, there is minimum to no play on the axes. i have done my best, also, to keep the weight of the laser head the most centered and close to the x aluminium profile. Belt path is optimized and aligned with the frame.

BOM:

2040x600 (x2)
2020x600 (x3)
mgn12h x500mm (x3), optional: you can go for 550mm for the x but those are are to find
gt2 belt 6mm wide x 5m (2x2,5m)
gt2 toothed idlers 3mm i.d. (x6)
gt2 toothless idlers 5mm i.d (x2) because i didnt have 3mm i.d. toothless on hand but will update a newer version soon with 3mm i.d. ones.
gt2 16 teeth sprocket (for steppers)
0.9 nema17 steppers
2209/2208 stepper driver
your choice of board (im using arduino with a cnc shield)
15x10 cable drag chain
12v (5amp minimum) power supply
atomstack a5 laser head used for this project, if you need a different laserhead holder just let me know, in the meanwhile i will upload some more optional holder for the other brand so you could use your choice of laserhead.
item.author: steph-vezina

item.title: Engagement Ring Case with Lithophane Insert (Screws Required)
item.description:
Full model can be purchased and downloaded from my Cults3D page:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/jewelry/engagement-ring-case-with-lithophane-insert-screws-required

Made this beautiful engagement ring case for my fiancee last christmas, just in time for Christmas Eve proposal. Now, you can too!

Case dimensions 36mm (H) x 55mm (L) x 55mm (W) when closed.

Lid hinge is designed such that the lid can stay up-right to the casing body without generating too much friction. Click-snap feature along the tip edge of the lid. Sand it down as required, but I found mine one printed okay.

You can mount a lithophane portrait with dimensions of 35mm x 35mm x 3mm thick, at the back of the lid, then supported by the 2 layers of Lithophane support inserts and 3x M3 counter sunk screws.

I use this free lithophane maker here:
(https://lithophanemaker.com/Framed%20Lithophane.html)

The ring cushion will be a separate insert to the casing body. Best to be printed with TPU filament as it is elastic.

DISCLAIMER: Avoid printing the ring cushion with hard material, otherwise it can potentially scratch your ring.

Recommended ring dimensions for the current ring cushion design:

Width of the band all the way around = 2.2mm
Depth of band = 1.5mm
Outside diameter = 19.5mm
Height from top of diamond to outside base of shank = 24mm

Following screws will be required to complete the assembly:
2 x Pan Head Screws M2.5 x 16mm long - for fixing the hinge.
3 x Counter Sunk Screws M3 x 6mm long - for fixing the lithophane on lid.

My case body and lid was printed using CCTREE Copper Filled PLA filament for elegant effect.
(https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B074W1WQL8/)

Apply few coats of Hycote spray for the fine polishing finish:
(https://www.amazon.co.uk/Hycote-Clear-Lacquer-400ml-Energy/dp/B004SNLNY2)
